Gunmen  Four officials of the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps have been abducted by suspected kidnappers along Itobe-Ajegu Road in Kogi State. This is happening barely 24 hours after 12 people were kidnapped from the state. The NSCDC officials were abducted with other civilians even though the number of civilians is unknown. According to reports, the officers were on their way to Benue State for promotion examinations and were in an official vehicle when they were abducted. The Kogi State Police Command confirmed the abduction.